## Plan: Add Pagination to `GET /users`

**Only one file changes: `src/routes.ts`**

### Current handler (lines 7–9)
```ts
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json(users);
});
```

### New handler
```ts
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1;
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10;

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);

  const start = (page - 1) * limit;
  const end   = start + limit;
  const data  = users.slice(start, end); // naturally [] when out of range

  res.json({
    data,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages },
  });
});
```

### Key decisions
| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `parseInt(...) \|\| default` | Handles missing, empty, or non-numeric query params cleanly |
| `users.slice(start, end)` | When `start >= 15` (out-of-range page), JS returns `[]` automatically — no extra branch needed |
| `GET /users/:id` untouched | No test changes, no logic changes |

